[http://www.trendnet.com/products/proddetail.asp?prod=235_TEW-712BR&cat=173 Product page]
[http://www.trendnet.com/downloads/list_subcategory.asp?SUBTYPE_ID=1580 Downloads] Cameo's FCC ID is NHPWLN2229. TRENDnet's FCC ID is XU8TEW712BR and is presumably the FCC ID printed on the unit label. AR1311-AL1A [http://www.smallnetbuilder.com/wireless/wireless-news/31887-trendnet-announces-overpriced-n150-router TRENDnet Announces Overpriced N150 Router - SmallNetBuilder] This device is listed on the [http://wiki.openwrt.org/toh/start#trendnet OpenWrt ToH] as supported after changes [https://dev.openwrt.org/changeset/33231/trunk 33231] and [https://dev.openwrt.org/changeset/33234/trunk 33234] :The CPU listed in the ToH is presumably what it is recognized under a OpenWrt Linux build - AR9330. This would seem to indicate the AR1311 is identical to the AR9331 / Hornet. ==Images== Image:TEW-712BR.jpg|angled Image:TEW-712BR_front.jpg|front Image:TEW-712BR_side.jpg|side Image:TEW-712BR_back.jpg|back Image:box_TEW-712BR.jpg|box, US Image:box_TEW-712BR_UK.jpg|box, UK [[Has images::external| ]][[Has images::packaging| ]]
